<subSubSection id="A7CC2DBDFFC5FFD1FF8DFBEBFCEBFEC3" lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="307" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFC5FFEEFF8DFBEBFBFFFB14" blockId="31.[113,1089,1037,1604]" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFF8DFBEBFF5EFB94" bold="true" box="[113,224,1037,1060]" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Remarks.</emphasis>
The species was unknown to subsequent authors and was listed only in catalogues. 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC5FFEEFF69FBCBFE92FBF4" author="SPAETH" box="[149,300,1069,1092]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" refId="ref50998" refString="SPAETH F. 1914: Chrysomelidae: 16. Cassidinae. In: SCHENKLING S. (ed.): Coleopterorum Catalogus. Pars 62. W. Junk, Berlin, 180 pp." type="book" year="1914">SPAETH (1914)</bibRefCitation>
transferred 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFE50FBCBFD18FBF4" authorityName="Baly" authorityYear="1869" box="[428,678,1069,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Mesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="honorata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFE50FBCBFD18FBF4" box="[428,678,1069,1092]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Mesomphalia honorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFD34FBCBFC1BFBF4" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1901" box="[712,933,1069,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Pseudomesomphalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFD34FBCBFC1BFBF4" box="[712,933,1069,1092]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Pseudomesomphalia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(= 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFC35FBCBFBB4FBF4" baseAuthorityName="BOROWIEC" baseAuthorityYear="1999" box="[969,1034,1069,1092]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFC35FBCBFBB4FBF4" box="[969,1034,1069,1092]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Stolas</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) and 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC5FFEEFF8DFBABFE8BFBD4" author="BOROWIEC" box="[113,309,1101,1124]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC (1999a)</bibRefCitation>
to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFEA5FBABFDC3FBD4" authority="Chevrolat, 1836" authorityName="Chevrolat" authorityYear="1836" box="[345,637,1101,1124]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFEA5FBABFE7BFBD4" box="[345,453,1101,1124]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Cyrtonota</emphasis>
Chevrolat, 1836
</taxonomicName>
. I had the opportunity to examine its 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFC5FFEEFBEFFBABFBFFFBD4" box="[1043,1089,1101,1124]" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">type</typeStatus>
and found that in fact this species belongs to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFDA9FB8BFCD7FB34" authority="Weise, 1896" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1896" box="[597,873,1133,1156]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Goniochenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFDA9FB8BFD61FB34" box="[597,735,1133,1156]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Goniochenia</emphasis>
Weise, 1896
</taxonomicName>
as it has three basal shiny and nearly glabrous antennomeres while species of Mesomphaliini have four or more.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFC5FFD1FF6CFB4BFC03FEA3" blockId="31.[113,1089,1037,1604]" lastBlockId="32.[151,1127,220,403]" lastPageId="32" lastPageNumber="307" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">
The species belongs to the subgenus 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFDEFFB4BFCBFFB74" authority="Weise, 1899" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1899" box="[531,769,1197,1220]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Goniochenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Baranosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFDEFFB4BFDC7FB74" box="[531,633,1197,1220]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Baranosa</emphasis>
Weise, 1899
</taxonomicName>
as it does not have large spots formed by dense pubescence on elytra and it is most similar to 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFD0DFB2BFC49FB54" authority="(Spaeth, 1928)" baseAuthorityName="Spaeth" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[753,1015,1229,1252]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Calaspidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discors">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFD0DFB2BFCE4FB54" box="[753,858,1229,1252]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">G. discors</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC5FFEEFC9AFB2BFC4EFB54" author="Spaeth" box="[870,1008,1229,1252]" firstAuthor="Spaeth" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" pagination="29 - 47" refId="ref51238" refString="SPAETH F. 1928: Mitteilungen ueber die Cassidinen des Prager Nationalmuseums II (Col. Chrysomelidae). Sbornik Entomologickeho Oddeleni Narodniho Musea v Praze 6: 29 - 47." type="journal article" year="1928">Spaeth, 1928</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFBDBFB2BFED2FAB4" authority="Hincks, 1956" authorityName="Hincks" authorityYear="1956" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Agenysa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFBDBFB2BFF65FAB4" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">G. peruviana</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC5FFEEFF1DFB0BFED2FAB4" author="Hincks" box="[225,364,1261,1284]" firstAuthor="Hincks" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" pagination="545 - 559" refId="ref49747" refString="HINCKS W. D. 1956: Some Neotropical Cassidinae (Col., Chrysomelidae) in the Museum G. Frey. Entomologischen Arbeiten aus dem Museum G. Frey 7: 545 - 559." type="journal article" year="1956">Hincks, 1956</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry id="97C13EA6FFC5FFEEFE55FB0BFE62FAB4" box="[425,476,1261,1284]" name="Peru" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Peru</collectingCountry>
, all sharing quite high postscutellar gibbosity. 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFC45FB0BFF6EFA94" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Baly" baseAuthorityYear="1869" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Goniochenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="honorata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFC45FB0BFF6EFA94" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Goniochenia honorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has lateral profile of elytra distinctly concave behind the postscutellar gibbosity and the latter is also distinctly higher than in 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFE0FFACBFDE0FAF4" baseAuthorityName="Spaeth" baseAuthorityYear="1928" box="[499,606,1325,1348]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Calaspidea" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discors">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFE0FFACBFDE0FAF4" box="[499,606,1325,1348]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">G. discors</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, which has the profile behind gibbosity nearly straight. 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFF32FAABFE19FAD4" authorityName="Spaeth" authorityYear="1928" box="[206,423,1357,1380]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Goniochenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="discors">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFF32FAABFE19FAD4" box="[206,423,1357,1380]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Goniochenia discors</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has dorsum mostly black with several yellow specks scattered over elytral disc with only a few reaching to explanate margin while 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFCB4FA8BFC77FA34" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Baly" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[840,969,1389,1412]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Goniochenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="honorata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFCB4FA8BFC77FA34" box="[840,969,1389,1412]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">G. honorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has a large oval spot in the middle of explanate margin of each elytron connected by narrow band across elytra and the pattern is reminiscent to that of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFDB0FA4BFCDBFA74" authority="(Spaeth, 1902)" baseAuthorityName="Spaeth" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[588,869,1453,1476]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Stolas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="zona">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFDB0FA4BFD7AFA74" box="[588,708,1453,1476]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Stolas zona</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC5FFEEFD2CFA4BFCE3FA74" author="Spaeth" box="[720,861,1453,1476]" firstAuthor="Spaeth" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" pagination="81 - 102" refId="ref50784" refString="SPAETH F. 1902: Neue Cassiden aus Peru. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift 1902: 81 - 102." type="journal article" year="1902">Spaeth, 1902</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. However, other species of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFF40FA2BFE9CFA54" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1899" box="[188,290,1485,1508]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Goniochenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Baranosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFF40FA2BFE9CFA54" box="[188,290,1485,1508]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Baranosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
display large variability in dorsal patterns and it is likely both species will be found to possess additional colour forms. So far, each species is known only from the 
<typeStatus id="306DC094FFC5FFEEFC23FA0BFB80F9B4" box="[991,1086,1517,1540]" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">holotype</typeStatus>
. According to the original description (
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFC5FFEEFDEDF9EBFD23F994" author="HINCKS" box="[529,669,1549,1572]" firstAuthor="HINCKS" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" pagination="545 - 559" refId="ref49747" refString="HINCKS W. D. 1956: Some Neotropical Cassidinae (Col., Chrysomelidae) in the Museum G. Frey. Entomologischen Arbeiten aus dem Museum G. Frey 7: 545 - 559." type="journal article" year="1956">HINCKS 1956</bibRefCitation>
), 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFD4FF9EBFC13F994" authorityName="Hincks" authorityYear="1956" box="[691,941,1549,1572]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Goniochenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="peruviana">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFD4FF9EBFC13F994" box="[691,941,1549,1572]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">Goniochenia peruviana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has similarly convex elytra and quite similar pattern and possibly is conspecific with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFC5FFEEFCACF9CBFC71F9F4" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Baly" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[848,975,1581,1604]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Goniochenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="31" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="honorata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFC5FFEEFCACF9CBFC71F9F4" box="[848,975,1581,1604]" italics="true" pageId="31" pageNumber="306">G. honorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. However, I have not examined its type and thus do not propose the synonymy. The remaining species of 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFAFFD1FF6BFF1AFF43FEA3" authorityName="Weise" authorityYear="1899" box="[151,253,252,275]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Goniochenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="306" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="subGenus" subGenus="Baranosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFAFFD1FF6BFF1AFF43FEA3" box="[151,253,252,275]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">Baranosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
have much less convex elytra, see key published by 
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFAFFD1FCDFFF1AFC07FEA3" author="SPAETH" box="[803,953,252,275]" firstAuthor="SPAETH" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" pagination="29 - 47" refId="ref51238" refString="SPAETH F. 1928: Mitteilungen ueber die Cassidinen des Prager Nationalmuseums II (Col. Chrysomelidae). Sbornik Entomologickeho Oddeleni Narodniho Musea v Praze 6: 29 - 47." type="journal article" year="1928">SPAETH (1928)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="EF697E36FFFAFFD1FF49FEFAFCEBFEC3" blockId="32.[151,1127,220,403]" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFAFFD1FF49FEFAFECBFE83" author="BOROWIEC" box="[181,373,284,307]" firstAuthor="BOROWIEC" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" refId="ref48283" refString="BOROWIEC L. 1999 a: A world catalogue of the Cassidinae (Coleoptera: Chrysomelidae). Biologica Silesiae, Wroclaw, 476 pp." type="book" year="1999" yearSuffix="a">BOROWIEC (1999a)</bibRefCitation>
synonymized 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFAFFD1FDF0FEFAFCD2FE83" authority="(Spaeth, 1932)" baseAuthorityName="Spaeth" baseAuthorityYear="1932" box="[524,876,284,307]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tutelata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFAFFD1FDF0FEFAFD73FE83" box="[524,717,284,307]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">Cyrtonota tutelata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFAFFD1FD26FEFAFCDBFE83" author="Spaeth" box="[730,869,284,307]" firstAuthor="Spaeth" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" pagination="182 - 204" refId="ref51336" refString="SPAETH F. 1932: Neue Cassiden (Col. Chrysom.). Stettiner Entomologische Zeitung 93: 182 - 204." type="journal article" year="1932">Spaeth, 1932</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
with 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFAFFD1FC59FEFAFB9BFE83" authorityName="Sekerka" authorityYear="2016" baseAuthorityName="Baly" baseAuthorityYear="1869" box="[933,1061,284,307]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Goniochenia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="honorata">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFAFFD1FC59FEFAFB9BFE83" box="[933,1061,284,307]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">G. honorata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
based on notes in unpublished manuscript of F. Spaeth but this synonymy is incorrect, see remarks under 
<taxonomicName id="28D605B5FFFAFFD1FF27FEBAFD8CFEC3" authority="(Baly, 1872)" baseAuthorityName="Baly" baseAuthorityYear="1872" box="[219,562,348,371]" class="Insecta" family="Chrysomelidae" genus="Cyrtonota" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delicosa">
<emphasis id="DDA2A224FFFAFFD1FF27FEBAFE18FEC3" box="[219,422,348,371]" italics="true" pageId="32" pageNumber="307">Cyrtonota delicosa</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="8B4703C7FFFAFFD1FE49FEBAFD95FEC3" author="Baly" box="[437,555,348,371]" firstAuthor="Baly" pageId="32" pageNumber="307" pagination="59 - 72" refId="ref47517" refString="BALY J. S. 1872: Descriptions of some species of Cassididae new to science. Transactions of the Entomological Society of London 1872: 59 - 72." type="journal article" year="1872">Baly, 1872</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
for additional information.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
